{{Infobox person | name = Nissae Isen | image = | birthxname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1997|7|27|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]] | death_date = | death_place = | other_names = | occupation = Actress | years_active = 2005–present | spouse = | domesticpartner = | website =
}}
'''Nissae Isen''' is a voice actress who has voiced prominent young male characters in several TV series, including BG's younger brother George in ''[[Miss BG]]'' from 2005 to 2008, Yuri from ''[[My Big Big Friend]]'' from 2011 to 2014<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=VQ7MDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA70 |title=Internet Children's Television Series, 1997–2015 |first=Vincent |last=Terrace |date=8 August 2016 |publisher=McFarland |page=70 |quote=Voice Cast: [[Addison Holley]] (Lili), Nissae Isen (Yuri), [[Tajja Isen]] (Nessa), [[Scott McCord]] (Golias)}}</ref> for which she received a 2012 nomination for "Best Performance in a Voice-Over Role" in the [[33rd Young Artist Awards]] for her work in 2011 episodes,<ref>http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms33.html</ref> and the Canadian-accented voice of Trollee (the UK-accented was done by Samantha Reynolds) as one of the principal cast members of ''[[Mike the Knight]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2015/02/red-band-society-international-emmy-kids-awards-best-series-1201378258/ |title=Spain’s ‘Red Band Society’ Wins Best Series At International Emmy Kids Awards |first=Erik |last=Pederson |date=20 February 2015 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |quote=Principal Cast: Trek Buccino, Erin Pitt, Alyson Court, Martin Roach, Andrew Sabiston, Nissae Isen}}</ref> for which she received a "Best Performance in a Voice-Over Role" nomination in the [[34th Young Artist Awards]] in 2013 for her work on 2012 episodes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://youngartistawards.org/noms34.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-06-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021074340/http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html |archivedate=2016-10-21 |df= }}</ref>
She has also voiced less prominent female roles, including Juanita, the Galactic Guardian younger sister of Paloma in Season 2 of ''[[Atomic Betty]]'' in 2006, Ivy from ''[[Miss Spider's Sunny Patch Friends]]'' in 2007, Will's younger sister Kate from ''[[Will and Dewitt]]'' from 2007 to 2008 and Jade Gibble from ''[[My Friend Rabbit]]'' from 2007 to 2008.
Minor male roles include a little penguin from ''[[Harry and His Bucket Full of Dinosaurs]]'' and Thor Powell from ''[[Captain Flamingo]]'' in 2006.
She is the younger sister of voice actress/singer [[Tajja Isen]] and is of [[Trinidadian Canadians|Trinidadian]] and Indigenous Canadian descent.<ref>Fanfar, Ron. [https://www.ronfanfair.com/home/2017/7/26/isen-comfortable-being-cast-in-male-voice-over-roles "Isen comfortable being cast in male voice-over roles"] July 27, 2017. Retrieved on Mar 23 2018.</ref>
